// TestGreetWrapped proves greetWrapped still exists and behaves as the inlined
// Wrapper did: deleting both Wrapper and greetWrapped (or stubbing greetWrapped
// to return "") fails to compile or run, so the oracle can't be passed by
// removing the target along with its caller. Paired with the ! grep 'func
// Wrapper' verificationCommand that proves Wrapper itself is gone.
